1
00:00:05,476 --> 00:00:07,040
Think of the Sun.

2
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:13,522
The Sun, its capacity to give
heat and light.

3
00:00:13,806 --> 00:00:16,042
[Sunlike Magnitude of Beauty]

4
00:00:16,119 --> 00:00:18,724
The magnitude of the Sun is infinite.

5
00:00:18,724 --> 00:00:21,889
We’re 93 million miles away

6
00:00:21,889 --> 00:00:28,184
or 150 million kilometres
away from the Sun,

7
00:00:29,060 --> 00:00:33,111
and we can feel sometimes—
we’re in Thailand, [laughing]

8
00:00:33,111 --> 00:00:39,833
and we can feel how hot it is
from 150 million kilometres away.

9
00:00:39,943 --> 00:00:44,589
So then what it would be like to go
to the centre of the Sun?

10
00:00:44,589 --> 00:00:48,439
Long before we get there 
we’ll disintegrate.
 

11
00:00:48,439 --> 00:00:52,559
So we can understand
something in comparison,
 

12
00:00:52,559 --> 00:01:01,013
the magnitude of Kṛṣṇa’s intensity
of beauty, love, charm, and sweetness.
 

13
00:01:01,013 --> 00:01:03,673
Sunlike magnitude.

14
00:01:03,673 --> 00:01:07,181
So there’s a particular position 
to be situated

15
00:01:07,181 --> 00:01:10,438
where we’ll be nourished by that.
 

16
00:01:10,438 --> 00:01:15,650
So we’re told, “Under the shelter
of the āśraya-vigraha.”
 

17
00:01:15,754 --> 00:01:20,039
Just like there’s certain metal
you put in a pot for smelting,

18
00:01:20,039 --> 00:01:22,390
where they melt, 
they create iron.

19
00:01:22,390 --> 00:01:24,481
You put iron in
and make steel.

20
00:01:24,481 --> 00:01:27,754
The pot doesn’t melt,
but what’s inside melts.
 

21
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:30,391
So the pot’s 
made out of harder stuff.

22
00:01:30,391 --> 00:01:33,996
So the chit-śakti, 
they’re made out of harder stuff,

23
00:01:33,996 --> 00:01:38,578
and ultimately guru goes towards 
the chit-śakti section—

24
00:01:38,578 --> 00:01:40,663
the āśraya-vigraha.
 

25
00:01:40,663 --> 00:01:46,833
So jīva has to always be under the shelter
of guru, the āśraya-vigraha,

26
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:51,698
to be nourished by the magnitude
of intensity of Kṛṣṇa conception.

27
00:01:51,698 --> 00:01:55,480
Remove the āśraya, 
the water …

28
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,573
If you take away the water,

29
00:01:57,573 --> 00:02:03,177
that Sun that was nourishing the lotus
will burn the lotus.

30
00:02:03,192 --> 00:02:07,354
The lotus, ‘ambuja’, it needs
to be situated in water.

31
00:02:07,354 --> 00:02:09,137
Then the Sun thrives.

32
00:02:09,137 --> 00:02:10,285
That’s the example.
 

33
00:02:10,285 --> 00:02:17,080
So the śisya-lotus situated safely
in the water, sheltered by guru,

34
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:20,945
the Kṛṣṇa-sun, Kṛṣṇa conception,
will nourish.

35
00:02:20,945 --> 00:02:27,181
Remove guru,
and the same thing will burn.
 

36
00:02:27,539 --> 00:02:33,306
So we’re nowhere without guru;
we have no individual capacity

37
00:02:33,306 --> 00:02:37,374
to approach Kṛṣṇa, 
or Kṛṣṇa conception.

38
00:02:39,608 --> 00:02:43,239
And so we see sahajiya imitation— 
it’s another …

39
00:02:43,378 --> 00:02:47,744
Saying so many things about Kṛṣṇa
from this book, that book …

40
00:02:47,744 --> 00:02:50,277
and all to their detriment. 
 

41
00:02:50,277 --> 00:02:52,324
Mayavadis taking the Name of Kṛṣṇa,

42
00:02:52,324 --> 00:02:55,844
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur saying
it’s like thunderbolts—

43
00:02:55,844 --> 00:03:02,099
the sound of their Kṛṣṇa-nam is like
thunderbolts striking the heart of Kṛṣṇa.

44
00:03:02,099 --> 00:03:09,564
So Kṛṣṇa conception is only extended 
through sādhu, śāstra, guru, Vaiṣṇava.

45
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:19,534
All others are fictitious, 
bogus, imaginary.
 

46
00:03:19,660 --> 00:03:24,966
Kṛṣṇa Himself says, “Those who say
they are My devotees directly,

47
00:03:24,966 --> 00:03:27,294
they’re not My real devotees.

48
00:03:27,294 --> 00:03:31,855
My real devotees are those 
who are devotees of My devotees.”

49
00:03:31,970 --> 00:03:35,994
That’s the secret to devotion. 
 

